<p>We have a Command Based robot, and our autonomous mode likes to throw the “Output not updated often enough” for the drivetrain.</p>
<p>I believe it’s because we don’t update the drivetrain when we aren’t using it. What am I missing?</p>
<p>Essentially, the autonomous mode is something like “shoot, move robot, pick up ball, move robot back, shoot” based on a bunch of sequential commands.</p>
<p>However, when we are shooting/waiting and not moving, we don’t send any updates to the drivetrain. How can we properly program the robot to fix this?</p>
